From readme:

> 19.20 Avoid multiple empty lines, only allow one newline at the end of files, and avoid a newline at the beginning of files. eslint: no-multiple-empty-lines

Which has a *bad* example:

```js
// bad - multiple empty lines
var x = 1;


var y = 2;
```

Currently, max empty lines [is set to 2](https://github.com/airbnb/javascript/blob/eslint-config-airbnb-v18.1.0/packages/eslint-config-airbnb-base/rules/style.js#L316) and above example passes as a correct one. Same goes for other useless empty lines - between function declarations, etc.

As seen by [comparing changes](https://github.com/facebook/react/commits/master/packages/eslint-plugin-react-hooks) between `eslint-plugin-react-hooks@2.4.0` and `3.0.0`:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/14854048/78947613-2587ee00-7ac6-11ea-8e64-957827912613.png)

The only breaking change seems to be https://github.com/facebook/react/commit/d3368beeecb2b51f51814f95f977e8c11900f54e. Also, a notable change is that a recommended configuration [has been added](https://github.com/facebook/react/commit/79a25125b19c2d6deaf03d4ab0dfdd6082377d97):

```js
export const configs = {
  recommended: {
    plugins: ['react-hooks'],
    rules: {
      'react-hooks/rules-of-hooks': 'error',
      'react-hooks/exhaustive-deps': 'warn',
    },
  },
};
```

It's almost identical to [the current rules in place](https://github.com/airbnb/javascript/blob/06b3ab11d9a443ff46f052dd00375e271e5146e6/packages/eslint-config-airbnb/rules/react-hooks.js#L12-L20), as applicable by extending `airbnb/hooks`. The list of available rules hasn't changed since v2, hence no additional changes should be required.

Fixes #2231.

